article.headline: High Point 93, Ohio Valley 48
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Mike Jefferson scored 19 points, including five 3-pointers, to lead High Point to a 93-48 rout of Ohio Valley on Saturday. Jefferson went 7-of-13 from the floor for the Panthers (4-3), going 5-of-6 from 3-point range. Jerald Minnis added a career-best 14 points and Landon Quick had 10 for High Point. Caleb Canton led the Fighting Scots (2-3) with nine points and 11 rebounds, while Chris LeBorious added 10 rebounds. High Point scored the game's first points and held Ohio Valley scoreless for nearly four minutes on the way to a 20-10 lead at the 11:26 mark. The Fighting Scots narrowed it to six points, but the Panthers went on a 17-2 run over the final five minutes for a 47-23 halftime lead. High Point scored the first eight points of the second half and led by 30 or more points the rest of the game. Every Panther who dressed for the game saw playing time, and 11 players chipped in points.
